    "created_at": "2016-10-13T15:32:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-13T15:32:24Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "#8239 is the first piece of the implementation, whereby we'll limit gross buffer usage - but only crudely by either delaying allocations or cancelling requests when overflow memory.\n\nI'll be following up in the coming months with additional smarts to reduce flow control windows dynamically based on memory pressure.\n\nUser control will be available by declaring pools and attaching them to servers or client channels at creation time. Pools will be dynamically resizable, with the guarantee that if the pool is resized there'll be a monotonic decrease in memory until the new size is reached.\n"
